{
  "stem": "1965.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 86.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the other one he has kept in perpetual-- what-- how should I say that-- a forever stigma of what your leader has done in the world with his war.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Do you know that man, who was so pro Nazi and so, [? actung ?] like, became meek after three and a half hours of discussion.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then the following day in Kiel Germany, when we arrived, when we were descending the walkway from the boat, the young man called out my name and asked to speak with me before we leave.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He says, I want you to know, I could not sleep the whole night because of what you said.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Thank you for enlightening.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I will transfer the message to other Germans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The reason I bring this up is, we who suffered, and we who have other descendants beyond us, who learned first-hand from us, we must never, never sit in the seat of God in judgment.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "What we must do is learn to communicate, understand why the human mind does something like this and so it shall never, ever happen again.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But it does happen again.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Prove again.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "There is another country in the world-- I'm trying to remember the name of that country right now.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I'm a little blanked out-- where a-- at least over a million people were exterminated, someplace in the orient.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I can't remember right now the name.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they backed their calendar to zero.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And that was, I believe, in the '70s.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Cambodia.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Thank you.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So you see, history repeats itself.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If not by the Germans, then by the Cambodian.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Not the Cambodian, then the Rwandans.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we must explore truly why we, the human race, are continuing on the same vein that happened in Germany.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
